HEADWORD: Cammock
<hw>Cam"mock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>cammoc</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant having long
hard, crooked roots, the <spn>Ononis spinosa</spn>; -- called also
<altname>rest-harrow</altname>. The <spn>Scandix Pecten-Veneris</spn> is
also called <ex>cammock</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

